<font color="#FF0000">VIET NAM: DON'T ASK/DON'T TELL</font><br>
<tt>Tue Nov 26 19:14:08 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
It has been over 24 years since my return from my second<br>
tour in 'Nam.  Still no one asks about it.  Even if I mention having been there, no one asks.  Either everyone is too timid to bring up the subject, afraid they might bring back bad memories or they just don't want to hear about it.<br>
You'd think after this length of time, people would be more comfortable with the subject.  <br><br>
Viet Nam is taboo.
<p><code>-- jrcall@mindspring.com  (Ron Callahan) </code><p>


